summary: Every time YouTubers decide to do a fanfiction reading I dread it because 99.9% of the time it’s them making fun of the fics and...
body:
Every time YouTubers decide to do a fanfiction reading I dread it because 99.9% of the time it’s them making fun of the fics and they tend to choose m/m or f/f fics to read.

Not to be that person, but it feels so insidious to me. I know fanfiction to people who don’t actively write or consume it has the reputation of being bad or a joke and while yes, some is bad, most are well written and even the bad ones have love put into it more often than not.

The reason I hate that they do this is because the majority of people who write fanfic are teen girls and LGBT+ people. By actively making fun of and overreacting to fics you’re putting down both groups which may have overlap in many cases. It’s sexism and homophobia.

Many people get their start in fanfiction. Many people use fanfiction as a way to cope. Many people use fanfiction to better their own writing and to explore topics with familiar characters.

I hate that YouTubers like to poke fun at them.
